[h3 id=Glitches
 
	" Glitches
	$LF
]h3
[h4 id=Infinitejump
 
	" Infinite jump
	$LF
]h4
[p 
	"The infinite jump glitch allows to use the double jump at will, following this input sequence:
	$LF
	"DLB/DRC/DLB/DRC...This is to execute during a spinning jump. Your Y speed is kept capped which means, among other
	$LF
	"things, that rising or going in a zigzag pattern amounts to the same result. This is only doable with
	$LF
	"the sword or grappling hook.
	$LF
]p
[h4 id=Warriorglitch
 
	" Warrior glitch
	$LF
]h4
[p 
	"The warrior glitch allows to use a weapon which we do not possess for a short amount of time. By
	$LF
	"following this input sequence:
	$LF
	"LB/DLC/LB/URA/UL/ULB (hold ULB)
	$LF
	".. we are able to get the axe!To execute this glitch, it is needed to have another weapon in your inventory, for example the
	$LF
	"scythe; you will be able to use the axe with the properties of the scythe. This glitch is not usable if
	$LF
	"we obtain the axe.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	[a class=extlink href=http://i.imgur.com/DrldKJw.png?1 rel=nofollow 
		"http://i.imgur.com/DrldKJw.png?1
	]a
	$LF
]p
[p 
	[a class=extlink href=http://i.imgur.com/UT7fuSM.png?1 rel=nofollow 
		"http://i.imgur.com/UT7fuSM.png?1
	]a
	$LF
]p
[p 
	[a class=extlink href=http://i.imgur.com/zSpQjWY.png?1 rel=nofollow 
		"http://i.imgur.com/zSpQjWY.png?1
	]a
	$LF
]p
[p 
	[a class=extlink href=http://i.imgur.com/FjYMH2n.png?1 rel=nofollow 
		"http://i.imgur.com/FjYMH2n.png?1
	]a
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"To do the glitch in the opposite direction, simply reverse the directional inputs,
	$LF
	"for example:
	$LF
	"RB/DRC/RB/ULA/UR/URB (hold URB)
	$LF
	"When the glitch is in place, we could as well input RB/RDB, holding RDB; RB will hit once with
	$LF
	"the current weapon while RDB will apply a new weapon change.
	$LF
]p
[h4 id=Maximumdamage
 
	" Maximum damage
	$LF
]h4
[p 
	"It is possible to apply the damage of a more powerful weapon than swords with this input sequence,
	$LF
	"assuming we have the sword or grappling cane in hand:
	$LF
	"RC/_/_/_/RA/RC/RBC (with _ standing for a blank input)
	$LF
	"I had noticed that if I made a jump with the sword or the grappling cane, the player would be able to
	$LF
	"execute a double jump, even with a weapon change. This way, the only thing that counts is to do a
	$LF
	"jump with the sword or grappling cane since the game will automatically make us benefit from a
	$LF
	"double jump; we will only need to do a weapon change and a double roll attack to obtain this result.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	[a class=extlink href=http://i.imgur.com/QKwoFad.png?1 rel=nofollow 
		"http://i.imgur.com/QKwoFad.png?1
	]a
	$LF
]p
[p 
	[a class=extlink href=http://i.imgur.com/NwaTNuP.png?1 rel=nofollow 
		"http://i.imgur.com/NwaTNuP.png?1
	]a
	$LF
]p
[pre 
	$LF
]pre
[p 
	[a class=extlink href=http://i.imgur.com/XHIAdOG.png?1 rel=nofollow 
		"http://i.imgur.com/XHIAdOG.png?1
	]a
	$LF
]p
[p 
	[a class=extlink href=http://i.imgur.com/DAY62kJ.png?1 rel=nofollow 
		"http://i.imgur.com/DAY62kJ.png?1
	]a
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"In these pictures, I start from a roll in the direction of a pit to do a double jump, which means my
	$LF
	"inputs will be a little bit different to have the same effects. If we compare the two last pictures, we
	$LF
	"can see that I have circled a value in red which is 4098, versus 4610 on the other picture; these
	$LF
	"represent the boss’s HP and tells us that the damage of this sword hit is 512 instead of 256; thedamage is effectively doubled.
	$LF
]p
[h4 id=Teleportationglitch(outofbounds)
 
	" Teleportation glitch (out of bounds)
	$LF
]h4
[p 
	"At the start of each level, the way the game loads the level is as follows: first Chakan, then the
	$LF
	"enemy sprites, before starting to load the level itself, loads the hitboxes of enemies and finishes to
	$LF
	"load the level. Knowing this, it is only needed that Chakan goes in an enemy’s hitbox and that the
	$LF
	"same hitbox finishes loading for the two to collide and Chakan to vanish. In reality, the game
	$LF
	"teleports us to an X,Y coordinate corresponding to the central point of the level (the center of the
	$LF
	"background); it is for this reason that I would take this glitch as a teleportation glitch rather than an
	$LF
	"out of bounds.
	$LF
]p
[h4 id=Elevator
 
	" Elevator
	$LF
]h4
[p 
	"Entering this input sequence while on ground:
	$LF
	"dc/_/dc/_/dc/_ ...
	$LF
	"we will see Chakan infinitely gain height! The Down + C inputs have the purpose, in normal
	$LF
	"gameplay, to go through a platform to reach a lower ground level. However, if we use the same
	$LF
	"input to try to go through solid ground which cannot be passed through, Chakan will start his
	$LF
	"animation by rising to go through the platform, before hitting the ground with his feet to show that
	$LF
	"it is impossible to go through. But cancelling this animation will make it so that Chakan only rises,
	$LF
	"and as such perpetually ascends. However, leaving the input blank every other frame has no other
	$LF
	"purpose; we will replace them with Up + B, which will give:
	$LF
	"dc/ub/dc/ub...
	$LF
	"and will have for effect to do an upward attack every other frame while gaining height.
	$LF
]p
