[h4 id=Level4.1:
 
	" Level 4.1:
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
]h4
[p 
	"Here we want to avoid the water because like in any self-respecting game of that era, it’s a burden
	$LF
	"that slows the character down.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"The pillars in that level can either go upwards or downwards; when trying a roll on one that goes
	$LF
	"upwards, you have to use it a little after the halfway point to make it optimal and go as far as
	$LF
	"possible, it doesn’t work on the ones going downwards.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"Getting 2 blue potions, then a clear one, and at last another blue.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"I’ve named that mini-boss “INFERNOCTOPUS” because it is the only one for which I had to go to
	$LF
	"the next level in order to find its RAM address: I needed to find another creature of this kind, then
	$LF
	"its address for the HP value and use that information for my benefit. Once taken care of, the passage
	$LF
	"leading to the grappling hook opens.
	$LF
]p
[h4 id=Level4.2:
 
	" Level 4.2:
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
]h4
[p 
	"It takes 5 hits with the mallet to break the wall at the beginning of the level, but I’ve managed to
	$LF
	"break it in 4 hits after multiple tries. The best explanation that I can come up with is that starting
	$LF
	"with the “maximum damage” trick, I got a bonus hit.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"The SPIDER-MICROCTOPUS boss gave me a really hard time, I had to find a perfect input
	$LF
	"sequence to get that result; the first step (and problem) is to pass under its totally abusive hitbox to
	$LF
	"get behind it. Afterwards, you can see me attacking while doing very specific jumps...
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"...In fact, when attacking during a jump phase, Chakan’s hitbox is shifted a little, a few pixels, and
	$LF
	"that made it possible to avoid taking damage.
	$LF
]p
[h4 id=Level4.3:
 
	" Level 4.3:
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
]h4
[p 
	"Activating the statue to open the pillar made of branches; this one pillar can’t be passed unless it is
	$LF
	"completely down, I succeeded at going through it when it starts opening because it automatically
	$LF
	"ejects Chakan in the opposite direction.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"Then you have to wait until one of the doors displays that token “ “ to pass; same for the next door,
	$LF
	"that leads us to the WATER-SNAKE boss.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"I hit him directly when he falls and hit one last time just before landing to be able to get to the other
	$LF
	"side and perform a frame perfect hit.
	$LF
